$ user_tab_columns / all_tab_columns / dba_tab_columns

Information about → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/columns[columns] of
→ development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables[tables],
→ development/databases/Oracle/objects/views[views] and
→ development/databases/Oracle/objects/clusters[clusters]

`dba_tab_columns` is related to → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/tab/cols[`dba_tab_cols`], the difference being that `dba_tab_columns` only shows columns that are
not generated. The definition of the view `dba_tab_columns` is:
code {
SELECT
   …
FROM
   DBA_TAB_COLS
from
   DBA_TAB_COLS
where
   USER_GENERATED = 'YES'"
code }

sa:
  Using `dba_tab_columns` to select the → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/columns/diff-structure[structural differences between two tables].

  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/tab/col_statistics[`xxx_TAB_COL_STATISTICS`]
